name.text: Creating histograms and frequency polygon for time spent on social media

questiontext.text:
A survey was conducted to find out how much time people spend on social media daily.

Time (minutes) Frequency Class width Midpoint Frequency density
0–10 {@freq[1]@} {@widths[1]@} [[input:m1]] [[validation:m1]][[feedback:prt_m1]] [[input:d1]] [[validation:d1]][[feedback:prt1]]
10–20 {@freq[2]@} {@widths[2]@} [[input:m2]] [[validation:m2]][[feedback:prt_m2]] [[input:d2]] [[validation:d2]][[feedback:prt2]]
20–30 {@freq[3]@} {@widths[3]@} [[input:m3]] [[validation:m3]][[feedback:prt_m3]] [[input:d3]] [[validation:d3]][[feedback:prt3]]
30–60 {@freq[4]@} {@widths[4]@} [[input:m4]] [[validation:m4]][[feedback:prt_m4]] [[input:d4]] [[validation:d4]][[feedback:prt4]]
60–120 {@freq[5]@} {@widths[5]@} [[input:m5]] [[validation:m5]][[feedback:prt_m5]] [[input:d5]] [[validation:d5]][[feedback:prt5]]

Once you have calculated the frequency densities, adjust the points on the graph so that the histogram and frequency polygon are correct.

[[jsxgraph]] var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, { boundingbox: [-5, 8, 130, -1], axis: true, showCopyright: false }); /* Data from STACK */ var lower = [0,10,20,30,60]; var upper = [10,20,30,60,120]; var mids = [{#midpoints[1]#},{#midpoints[2]#},{#midpoints[3]#},{#midpoints[4]#},{#midpoints[5]#}]; /* True densities */ var dens = [{#densities[1]#},{#densities[2]#},{#densities[3]#},{#densities[4]#},{#densities[5]#}]; /* Draw histogram rectangles */ for (let i=0; i<5; i++) { board.create('polygon', [ [lower[i],0], [upper[i],0], [upper[i],dens[i]], [lower[i],dens[i]] ], { fillOpacity: 0.2, withLines: false }); } /* Draggable frequency polygon points */ var pts = []; for (let i=0; i<5; i++) { pts.push( board.create('point', [mids[i], 1], { name: '', size: 3 }) ); } /* Connect points */ board.create('polygonalchain', pts); [[/jsxgraph]]
